Implementing blog based application
It has users
A user can create n posts
A post can have n number of categories
Implemented model mapper by creating external bean during initialisation of spring boot class
Implemented global exception handler
Implemented data bean validation
Implemented pagination (Pagination is used to limit the number of records to be displayed in a single page, rest records will be displayed as per the pagination configuration)
Spring Boot has all the support needed for pagination and sorting, since we extend JpaRepository, and JpaRepo can already accept Pageable
Improvised Pagination response by creating a custom class to send response details as pageNumber, current page number, page size etc
Implementing Sort By also, spring jpa provides support for sort by as well
Implementing searching by title
Implemented image upload and image serve API
Implemented comments on a post
Now going to implement securing Rest APIs with Spring Security